                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d187">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Mutual Guarantee (Locarno)/394:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-09T23:00:00-06:00"
                            >March 9, 1936—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 10—11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I venture to express the hope that opportunity may offer for the President to
                    tender good offices to avert war in Europe. If we had acted promptly in August,
                    1914, that catastrophe might have been averted or its tragedy ended earlier.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
